                <h1>The History of Alcoholics Anonymous: A Journey of Recovery</h1>
                <p>Alcoholics Anonymous (AA) was founded in 1935 by Bill Wilson and Dr. Bob Smith in Akron, Ohio, to aid individuals struggling with alcohol addiction. The organization introduced the 12-step program, emphasizing personal accountability, peer support, and spiritual growth. Over the decades, AA has expanded globally, helping millions achieve sobriety.</p>
